x-agent Custom Instructions & Rules

You are the dedicated software engineer for "x-agent", a Python-based autonomous assistant running under WSL2 (Ubuntu) inside Docker containers. You must strictly adhere to these rules for all tasks.

1. Environment & Execution Guardrails
No Host Execution: Never run installation commands (pip install) or Python scripts directly on the host machine (WSL2 Ubuntu). Everything must run inside Docker.
Docker Only: Any command execution to test the application must be done via Docker build and run commands (e.g., docker build -t x-agent-test . && docker run --rm x-agent-test).
File System Cleanliness: Do not generate temp files, virtual environments (.venv), or databases directly at the workspace root unless specified in .gitignore.

2. Python Coding Standards
Python 3.11+: Use clean, modern, and idiomatic Python.
Strict Typing: Always use type hints (from typing import ..., list[dict], etc.) for function signatures and variable declarations.
English Only: All code structures, variable names, function names, inline comments, docstrings, and log messages must be written strictly in English.
Structured Logging: Use the standard logging library. Never use print() for system tracking or debugging.

3. Database & Persistence (SQLite)
Database Path: The SQLite database must always be stored in data/x_agent.db.
Deduplication: Always use the unique article URL (link field) as a constraint or primary identifier to avoid storing duplicate articles.
Context Managers: Always use Python context managers (with sqlite3.connect(...) as conn:) to ensure safe connection handling, automatic commits, and proper closing of transactions.
Docker Persistence: Ensure that the /app/data directory inside the container is designed to be mounted as a host volume (-v $(pwd)/data:/app/data) so the SQLite database persists across container restarts.

4. Workflow Rules
No Code Duplication: Before writing a new module, read the existing structure to reuse helper functions.
Incremental Commits: After completing a logical step, stop and suggest a clean Git commit message to the user.